# retrieval-vs-computation — Cursor Rules

## Project
Research paper: "Beyond Accuracy" — behavioral + mechanistic signatures of retrieval-like
processing in LLMs. BITS Pilani, 2026. Target: BlackboxNLP / GenBench (EMNLP workshops).

## Language discipline (non-negotiable)
Never write "the model retrieves" or "the model reasons."
Always write "behavior consistent with retrieval-like processing."
This applies to code comments, docstrings, and any markdown.

## Repo structure
probes/contamination/   — Probe 3: Infini-gram pipeline
probes/probe1_surface/  — Probe 1: CSS variants + activation analysis
probes/probe2_plan_exec/— Probe 2: CCI/TEP + lens analysis
data/                   — frozen JSON problem sets, small CSVs only
results/                — one CSV per probe, always committed
scripts/                — shared utilities
notebooks/              — figures only, one per probe
paper/                  — LaTeX

## Code conventions
- Python 3.11, pandas + scipy + statsmodels only (no ML libs until Phase 2)
- Every API call wrapped in retry logic (tenacity)
- Every result saved to results/ as CSV immediately after computation
- No hardcoded API keys — always os.environ via dotenv
- Bootstrap CIs on every aggregate (10k resamples, scipy.stats)
- All random operations take an explicit seed parameter

## Models
- Mechanistic analysis: Qwen2.5-7B only (open weights)
- Behavioral: Qwen + one closed pair (TBD: GPT-4o/o3 or Claude Sonnet 3.5/3.7)
- Never attempt mechanistic analysis on closed models

## What Cursor should NOT do
- Do not suggest future-work sections
- Do not strengthen claims beyond "behavior consistent with"
- Do not add ML/HuggingFace imports until Phase 2 is explicitly started